---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Link from "@components/Link.astro";
import { ABOUT } from "@consts";
---

<Layout title={ABOUT.TITLE} description={ABOUT.DESCRIPTION}>
  <Container>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-5 sm:flex-row sm:items-start"
        style="padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);"
      >
        <img
          src="/images/headshot.png"
          alt="Adam M. Rahman"
          class="size-24 shrink-0 rounded-full object-cover"
          style="border: 1px solid var(--rule);"
        />
        <div>
          <h1 class="page-heading-sm">Adam Rahman</h1>
          <p class="body-text-sm" style="margin-top: 0.25rem;">
            Software engineer at IBM &middot; M.S. Computer Engineering, NYU
            Tandon &middot; B.A. CS & Theater, Wesleyan
          </p>
          <p class="body-text-xs" style="margin-top: 0.35rem;">
            Building tools for geospatial AI and humanitarian use. Poet and
            theatermaker with 34 productions and counting.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-layout">
        <article class="prose about-prose">
          <p>
            I'm a software engineer at <Link href="https://www.ibm.com/z" external
              >IBM</Link
            > in New York City, working on test automation and technology
            modernization for the IBM Z mainframe platform. I'm replacing legacy
            mainframe testing tools with modern open-source frameworks: porting
            <Link href="https://grafana.com/oss/k6/" external>Grafana k6</Link>
            natively to z/OS, building Locust-based load testing for 3270
            terminals, and creating CI/CD pipelines that bring modern DevOps
            practices to enterprise mainframe infrastructure.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm pursuing an M.S. in Computer Engineering at <Link
              href="https://engineering.nyu.edu/"
              external>NYU Tandon School of Engineering</Link
            > and a B.A. in Computer Science and Theater from <Link
              href="https://www.wesleyan.edu/"
              external>Wesleyan University</Link
            >, where I was a <Link
              href="https://www.wesleyan.edu/patricelli/"
              external>Patricelli Center Fellow</Link
            >. I also developed <Link
              href="https://wesleyanargus.com/2019/04/23/immersive-imaginary-exhibit-brings-augmented-reality-to-mac650/"
              external>SoundStoneVR</Link
            >, a spatial audio VR composition tool shown at Wesleyan's Immersive Imaginary exhibition.
          </p>
          <p>
            Outside of work, I build tools at the intersection of geospatial AI
            and humanitarian use. My project <Link href="/dev/dream-meridian"
              >DreamMeridian</Link
            > runs AI-powered geospatial queries entirely offline on a Raspberry
            Pi for refugee camps and disaster zones, placing 2nd out of 1,600+
            participants in the ARM AI Developer Challenge. I was also <Link
              href="https://engineering.nyu.edu/news/meet-adam-munawar-rahman-leveraging-ai-humanitarian-use"
              external>profiled by NYU Tandon Engineering</Link
            > for this work, and covered in <Link
              href="https://www.businessweekly.co.uk/posts/chuckit-takes-first-prize-in-arm-ai-developer-challenge"
              external>Business Weekly</Link
            >.
          </p>
          <p>
            This thread runs back to my time at UNICEF, where I built geospatial
            routing tools for school site planning, and through projects like <Link
              href="/dev/ariadne-nyc">AskStreets</Link
            > (GraphRAG for urban planning) and our climate-aware emergency routing
            tool for Brownsville, Brooklyn, which won Best Community Communication
            Tool at the LEAP Climate Hackathon at the American Museum of Natural
            History.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm also a poet and theatermaker. My poetry has been published in
            <Link href="https://heartonoursleeves.press" external
              ><em>Collide-oscope</em></Link
            > (Heart on Our Sleeves Press) and
            <Link href="https://www.fourtulips.com/archives/padma" external
              >Four Tulips</Link
            >, where I was a finalist in the Fantastic Mischief Writing Contest.
            On the theater side, I've produced 34 shows, directed Ayad Akhtar's
            <em>Disgraced</em> at Wesleyan, stage-managed <Link
              href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/03/theater/really-really-gorgeous-review.html"
              external>Really Really Gorgeous</Link
            > at <Link href="https://thetanknyc.org/" external>The Tank NYC</Link
            >, and worked as a sound, set, and <Link href="/design"
              >graphic designer</Link
            >. I also wrote theater criticism for <Link
              href="https://wesleyanargus.com/2017/11/13/gruesome-murders-hip-hop-breaks-totalitarian-states-the-pillowman-premieres-at-the-cfa-theater/"
              external>The Wesleyan Argus</Link
            >.
          </p>
        </article>

        <aside class="about-rail">
          <dl class="about-facts">
            <div class="fact-row">
              <dt>Based</dt>
              <dd>New York City</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="fact-row">
              <dt>Now</dt>
              <dd>IBM &middot; NYU Tandon</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="fact-row">
              <dt>GitHub</dt>
              <dd><Link href="https://github.com/msradam" external>msradam</Link></dd>
            </div>
            <div class="fact-row">
              <dt>LinkedIn</dt>
              <dd><Link href="https://linkedin.com/in/adamsrahman" external>adamsrahman</Link></dd>
            </div>
            <div class="fact-row">
              <dt>Medium</dt>
              <dd><Link href="https://medium.com/@msradam" external>@msradam</Link></dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 160px;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-rail {
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .about-facts {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .fact-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .fact-row:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .fact-row dt {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.611rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .fact-row dd {
    font-family: "Source Serif 4", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 0.833rem;
    color: var(--text-2);
    margin: 0.15rem 0 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .about-rail {
      order: -1;
    }
  }
</style>
